Re: Proof-of-work difficulty increasing

Bitcointalk

2010-02-25 23:06:29 UTC - [11]Original Post

   The formula is based on the time it takes to generate 2016 blocks.  The
   difficulty is multiplied by 14/(actual days taken).  For instance, this
   time it took 9.4 days, so the calculation was 14/9.4 = 1.49.  Previous
   difficulty 2.53 * 1.49 = 3.78, a 49% increase.
   I donʼt know what youʼre talking about accepting easier difficulties.
